STRINGTABLE
LANGUAGE LANG_JAPANESE, 0x1
{
  192, 	"Data folder could not be found.\r\nDo you want to create a new one?"
  193, 	"A minimal new game project has been created in the Data folder.\r\n\r\nWelcome to the world of the WOLF RPG Editor.\r\nEnjoy developing your game to a heart's content!"
  194, 	"Could not create Data folder.\r\nProcessing stopped."
  195, 	"Val."
  196, 	"Which initial data do you want to create,\r\nEmpty Data with Basic RPG System or Completely Empty Data?\r\n\r\n■ If you select \"Yes\"  [Empty Data with Base RPG System]\r\n - Common Event, User DB and Variable DB for the Base System\r\n - Title Map and Post-start Map\r\n - Pre-configured system images and sounds (SystemGraphic)\r\n - Some character images, monster images and background music material\r\n - Four pre-configured Tileset settings\r\n  Create a Data folder with the above RPG creation data.\r\n\r\n■ If you select \"No\"  [Completely Empty Data]\r\n - Only one start-up map\r\n - No materials, no data\r\n  Create a Data folder with the above empty data.\r\n\r\n■ If you select \"Cancel\"\r\n  Abort the process."
  197, 	"The basic data folder \"%s\" by the -basic option did not exist.\r\n\r\nStartup will be aborted."
  198, 	"The basic data folder has been changed to \"%s\" by the -basic option.\r\n\r\n*When editing this time, please replace the \"BasicData\" folder name in the error message with the \"%s\" folder to read."
  199, 	"The data you tried to open was older than Ver2, so the data conversion to Ver3 was attempted, but Editor could not be started because the -basic option was set.\r\nPlease restart without the -basic option.\r\n\r\n*Also, files containing basic data folders other than BasicData cannot be converted successfully."
  200, 	"ms (For MIDI, tick)"
  201, 	"File could not be saved.\r\n\r\n*Check the access permissions.\r\n*If the data is on a shared folder, it is often temporarily not writable"
  202, 	"Japanese (1) [Default];English (2);Western European (3);Chinese (Simplified) (4);Chinese (Traditional) (5);Korean (6);"
  203, 	"Export basic data (Game Settings, DB, Map, Common Events, Tileset Settings) as text to the \"%s\" folder.\r\nAre you sure?"
  204, 	"Export to TXT is complete!\r\n\r\n[Exported .Auto.txt files]\r\n%s"
  205, 	"\r\n[Other %d Files (All %d Files)]"
  206, 	"Import .Auto.txt files from the \"%s\" folder\r\nand overwrite basic data (Game Settings, DB, Map, Common Events, Tileset Settings).\r\nAre you sure?\r\n\r\n*This process may unintentionally import contents that are not as expected.\r\nIf you are unsure, drag and drop them one by one into each window while checking the contents."
  207, 	"Import all .mps.Auto.txt files from the \"%s\" folder\r\nand overwrite all map data (.mps).\r\nAre you sure?\r\n\r\n*This process may unintentionally import contents that are not as expected.\r\nIf you are unsure, drag and drop them into each window one by one while checking the contents."
}

