  11719, 	" Receive String"
  11720, 	"[Warning! Behavior will change drastically in Ver3!]\r\n\r\nDo you want to keep \"Adjust Game.exe Version\" in \"Basic Game Settings\" as \"Latest\"?\r\n\r\nIf any of the following apply, \"No\" is recommended.\r\n(If you select \"No\", it will be set to \"Run as Old Ver2.29\". You can change later.)\r\n\r\n●Using \"Get Chip ID\" of the \"Set Variable+\" command.\r\n●Using \"Overwrite Map Chips\" or \"Change Map Chip Settings\" of the \"Chip Management\" command.\r\n  → In these cases, the chip ID will shift\r\n       because the number of auto-tiles increased from 16 to 31,\r\n       so if you do not select \"No\" to keep the old behavior,\r\n       it may not work as expected!!\r\n\r\n●Using \"Keyboard Input\" of the \"Set String\" command.\r\n  → One Japanese character has changed from 2 bytes to 3 bytes,\r\n       so the number of characters will be insufficient.\r\n       If you select \"No\", the number of input characters will be modified by 1.5 times.\r\n\r\n●Otherwise, if you want to keep the previous behavior rather than use the new features, \"No\" is recommended."
