  11811, 	"Notes on Label!"
  11812, 	"If you insert a Debug Text with the following command,\r\nthe information will be displayed in \"Debug Window\"\r\nwhen the game is run.\r\n (Enter only one line, with correct case)\r\n\r\nValWatch:ON=2000009\r\n→　After execution, monitors the value\r\n　　of normal variable 9 (2000009)\r\n　　and displays the value after it has been changed.\r\n\r\nPictureWatch:ON=123\r\n→　After execution, monitors picture 123 \r\n　　and displays information\r\n　　when the picture has been processed."
  11813, 	"Debug Text Command Tricks"
  11814, 	"Data could not be loaded because it is protected by a protection that is newer than the current version.\r\n\r\nPlease update Editor to the latest version."
  11815, 	"■Game.exe  Ver3.310\r\n  ●Fixed a bug where waiting time did not occur when \"Wait\" was executed during \"Prepare Transition\".\r\n  If you want to revert to the old behavior, set the version adjustment to \"Run as Old Ver3.300\" (\"Wait\" during \"Prepare Transition\" will be almost disabled).\r\n  ●Pixel Move is now in beta. In the old alpha version of Pixel Move, direction changes and animations did not work with 4-way graphics, but did work with 8-way graphics, and T/TX character graphics did not animate with either 4-way or 8-way graphics.\r\n  You can revert to that behavior by setting the version adjustment to \"Run as Old Ver3.300\" or earlier."
  11816, 	"Files are protected, but there is no protection key information in Editor.ini!\r\nPlease enter the protection key again."
  11817, 	"In Ver3.31, the data format of the core files was changed,\r\nso backups were created in the \"AutoBackup_Before_Ver3.31\" folder in the BasicData folder.\r\n(Game.dat, CommonEvent.dat, DataBases, TileSet.dat)\r\n\r\n*If you want to revert to the old version of the EXE,\r\n  copy these backup files and overwrite the ones in the BasicData folder."
