  11916, 	"■Game.exe  Ver3.50\r\n●The display interval of special characters p[?], [?], and mg[?] is now faster.\r\n●\"DB Management\" now flexibly converts between numbers and strings (old behavior caused an error).\r\n●When a picture is erased with a duration of 0 frames, the picture information now cannot be gotten by Set Variable+ immediately afterwards. (In the old behavior, the picture information can be gotten by Set Variable+ during the same frame that the picture was erased over 0 frames.)\r\n●When a character's body graphic is erased by the \"Change Character Chip\" command of \"Effects\", all layers are now erased. (In the old behavior, all layers disappeared visually, but the overlay layers remained internally.)\r\n●\"Event ID at Mouse Position\" in \"Other\" of Set Variable+ now takes map zoom into account. (In the old behavior, it does not take map zoom into account.)\r\n●When an event touches the hero by \"Approach Event\" or \"Approach Position\" commands of \"Move Route\", the event is now triggered by \"Event Touch\". (In the old behavior, these two commands do not activate Event Touch.)\r\n●When the hero touches an event by Move Route in \"Parallel Process\", the event is now triggered by \"Player Touch\". (In the old behavior, \"Player Touch\" is not activated when an event is touched by Move Route.)\r\n●Fixed a bug where the pause cursor goes out of screen when a large value is set in \"Sys6:Pause Cursor Y\" for 320x240 screen resolution.\r\n●Fixed a bug where \"Event Touch\" events placed at position (0,0) were triggered once after startup or during loading.\r\n●Fixed a bug where scroll-linked pictures were not displayed in the expected position after a certain loop.\r\n●When a forced picture pattern is overwritten by \"Character\" in \"Effects\", the pattern value returned by \"Set Variable+\" is now also changed during the same frame. (In the old behavior, it is delayed by one frame.)\r\n●The graphic of an event with a tile chip can now also be changed by \"Change Character Chip\" in \"Character\" of \"Effects\". (In the old behavior, the graphic of an event with a tile chip cannot be changed.)\r\n●Fixed a bug where the run state was stuck when \"Reserved\" and \"Confirm Key / Touch\" events were triggered in the same frame.\r\n●Fixed a bug where if the game was saved while talking to a map event, it remained the same direction after loading and cannot be restored.\r\n●Fixed a bug where the cursor width of a Choice is smaller than the character width when the character spacing was reduced by \\-[?], etc.\r\n●Fixed a bug where if a string picture is set to an empty string, its image size returned by Set Variable+ remained the previous value.\r\n●Fixed a bug where \"Passable (Tile & Event)\" of Set Variable+ was used for a 0.5x1 event, and only the head side was hit, not the foot side.\r\n●\"Get Type/Data/Field Number\" of DB Management now return -1 if a nonexistent name is specified. (In the old behavior, they return 0 after the error message.)\r\n  →  If you want to revert to the old behavior, set the version adjustment to \"Run as Old Ver3.390\" or earlier."
  11917, 	"Do you want to open the keyboard \"Keycode List\" page in your browser?\r\n\r\nhttps://silversecond.com/WolfRPGEditor/Help/04ev_keyinput.html#keycode"
  11918, 	"In Ver<VER>, the data format of the core files changed,\r\nso backups were created in the \"AutoBackup_Before_Ver<VER>\" folder in the BasicData folder.\r\n(Game.dat, CommonEvent.dat, DataBases, TileSet.dat)\r\n\r\n*If you want to revert to the old version of the EXE,\r\n  copy these backup files and overwrite the ones in the BasicData folder."
  11919, 	"Map Event Y's Self X /1000000+10*Y+X"
}

